Two men have been arrested in Belhar, Cape Town for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition, and a “significant” amount of tik (crystal methamphetamine) respectively, Western Cape police said on Saturday.
Officers attached to “Operation Combat” conducted a vehicle check point (VCP) in Chestnut Way, Belhar on Friday afternoon, Captain FC Van Wyk said.
A white Toyota Quantum minibus taxi was stopped and searched during the VCP. Officers found a 9mm “short” firearm with 12 live rounds and a magazine in the possession of one man.
The 25-year-old man was arrested for illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition. Further investigation showed that the firearm was not registered.
Officers also arrested a 35-year-old man who was found with a “significant amount of tik” in his possession. Both arrested suspects were due to appear in the Bellville Magistrate’s Court on Monday, Van Wyk said.
